					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A boot logo when no cartridge inserted is surely doable. There are plently old Famiclones that had 'built-in' games that were actually a cartridge PCB inserted into a second slot at bottom side of the main PCB. It was connected 1-to-1 for the most part. Not sure what exactly should be done to replicate the same on the original NES. Guess detection of inserted cartridge was done through the pins that are short by inserted cartridge, and switch between them is by switching a line, maybe RD or something.</div>

